OL,3,CCritical infrastructure hit as risk of
OL,4,Cenergy shock rises
OL,6,FThe targeting of the oil and gas
OL,7,Ffields hasn't just sent the prices of
OL,8,Fboth up; it has sent the stock markets
OL,9,Fdown, as Economics Editor Joel Hill
OL,10,Freports
OL,12,FThe price of oil and gas has risen to
OL,13,Flevels that are feeding inflation
OL,14,Faround the world - but we are not yet
OL,15,Fat full crisis levels.
OL,17,FThat distinction matters. What happens
OL,18,Fnext will depend not just on prices,
OL,19,Fbut on how long disruption in the Gulf
OL,20,Fcontinues and how much damage is done
OL,21,Fto energy infrastructure.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1773943560
OL,3,CCritical infrastructure hit as risk of
OL,4,Cenergy shock rises
OL,6,FTonight, the Federal Reserve said it
OL,7,Fwill press ahead with plans to cut
OL,8,Finterest rates this year, noting it is
OL,9,F"too soon to know" how long this war
OL,10,Fwill last and what the lasting impact
OL,11,Fwill be.
OL,13,FFor now, markets are holding onto the
OL,14,Fassumption that the conflict will be
OL,15,Fcontained and that energy flows will
OL,16,Feventually resume.
OL,18,FBut that assumption is becoming harder
OL,19,Fto sustain.
OL,26,@qD@AOUqD@RO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
